        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 5:56AM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 555 AM CDT, strong thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 11 miles northeast of Carson to 6 miles southwest of
Flasher. Movement was northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Flasher and St. Anthony.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
